body:
Hi guys!

First of all, thank you for your brilliant solution. It is awesome and we use it almost in every our project. We love it very much.

In one of the projects we need to use exceljs in browser, and it works perfectly in modern browsers (like chrome, ff, edge). But there are some problems using it in InternetExplorer10. We understand that the problem is with Uint8Array and it strange work in IE10.

How do you think, could you do something to enhance your solution with IE10 support?

Thank you for your work!

_Some screenshots and code. It fails on writeBuffer => write => ZipWriter=>finalize_

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7835251/37419697-17b38d66-27c6-11e8-838b-1d12ef3b1223.png)
``` JavaScript
    return (workbook.xlsx)
      .writeBuffer({ base64: true })
      .then(function(xls64) {
          var data = new Blob([xls64], {
              type: 'application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet'
          });
          if (model.filename) {
              return download(data, model.filename, 'application/excel');
          } else {
              return data;
          }
      });
```
